Description: Splitway interim egui GUI — a privilege-free IPC client over the daemon
 socket
 The Splitway desktop GUI: a privilege-free egui front-end that drives the
 splitway daemon over its control socket. Installing it adds an opt-in
 `splitway` group + a systemd drop-in so an in-group user can control split-DNS
 without sudo; the group starts empty, so the default posture is unchanged until
 you run `usermod -aG splitway <user>`. Requires the splitway package.

